# Firebase Security Rules

```javascript
rules_version = '2';
service cloud.firestore {
  match /databases/{database}/documents {
    
    // Helper function to check if user is authenticated
    function isAuthenticated() {
      return request.auth != null;
    }
    
    // Helper function to check if user is admin
    function isAdmin() {
      return isAuthenticated() && get(/databases/$(database)/documents/users/$(request.auth.uid)).data.role == 'admin';
    }
    
    // Helper function to check if user is the owner
    function isOwner(userId) {
      return isAuthenticated() && request.auth.uid == userId;
    }
    
    // Users collection
    match /users/{userId} {
      // Users can read their own document
      allow read: if isOwner(userId);
      // Admins can read all users
      allow read: if isAdmin();
      // Users cannot write to users collection directly
      allow write: if false;
    }
    
    // Volunteers collection
    match /volunteers/{volunteerId} {
      // Anyone can create a new volunteer registration
      allow create: if request.resource.data.email != null && request.resource.data.firstName != null;
      
      // Volunteers can read their own profile
      allow read: if isOwner(volunteerId) || isAdmin();
      
      // Volunteers can update their own profile
      allow update: if isOwner(volunteerId) && 
        !request.resource.data.keys().hasAny(['status', 'createdAt']); // Can't change status or creation date
      
      // Only admins can delete volunteers
      allow delete: if isAdmin();
    }
    
    // Projects collection
    match /projects/{projectId} {
      // Authenticated users can read projects
      allow read: if isAuthenticated();
      // Only admins can create/update/delete projects
      allow create, update, delete: if isAdmin();
    }
    
    // Assignments collection
    match /assignments/{assignmentId} {
      // Users can read their own assignments
      allow read: if isAuthenticated() && 
        (resource.data.volunteerId == request.auth.uid || isAdmin());
      // Only admins can create assignments
      allow create: if isAdmin();
      // Only admins can update assignments
      allow update: if isAdmin();
      // Only admins can delete assignments
      allow delete: if isAdmin();
    }
    
    // Activities collection
    match /activities/{activityId} {
      // Users can read activities related to them
      allow read: if isAuthenticated() && 
        (resource.data.volunteerId == request.auth.uid || isAdmin());
      // Volunteers can create their own activities
      allow create: if isAuthenticated() && 
        request.resource.data.volunteerId == request.auth.uid;
      // Only admins can update/delete activities or volunteers can update their own pending activities
      allow update: if isAdmin() || 
        (isOwner(resource.data.volunteerId) && resource.data.status == 'pending');
      // Only admins can delete
      allow delete: if isAdmin();
    }
    
    // Reports collection
    match /reports/{reportId} {
      // Only admins can read reports
      allow read: if isAdmin();
      // Only admins can create reports
      allow create: if isAdmin();
      // Only admins can update/delete reports
      allow update, delete: if isAdmin();
    }
    
    // Notifications collection
    match /notifications/{notificationId} {
      // Users can read their own notifications
      allow read: if isOwner(resource.data.userId);
      // Only backend can create notifications
      allow create: if false;
      // Users can mark their own notifications as read
      allow update: if isOwner(resource.data.userId) && 
        request.resource.data.keys() == resource.data.keys() - ['read'];
      // Users can delete their own notifications
      allow delete: if isOwner(resource.data.userId);
    }
    
    // Default: deny all other access
    match /{document=**} {
      allow read, write: if false;
    }
  }
}
```

## Rules Explanation

1. **isAuthenticated()**: Checks if user is logged in
2. **isAdmin()**: Checks if user has admin role
3. **isOwner(userId)**: Checks if current user matches the userId

### Collection Permissions

- **Users**: Protected - only users can read their own, admins can read all
- **Volunteers**: Semi-public - registration is open, but profile access is restricted
- **Projects**: Read-only for authenticated users, write-only for admins
- **Assignments**: Restricted by volunteer ID and admin access
- **Activities**: Restricted by volunteer ID with approval workflow
- **Reports**: Admin-only
- **Notifications**: User-specific access

---

## Testing Rules

Use Firebase Emulator Suite for local testing:

```bash
firebase emulators:start --only firestore
```

Write tests in `firestore.rules.test.js` to verify security rules.
